      "body": "**T5 (extract & prove Pic\u2070 `IdentityComponent`) has no unblocked closable sorry left \u2014 recommend running `AJC.picrep` next instead.**\n\nOpening Ground of run 0008 (focus `tasks=T5`) audited the target. `AlgebraicJacobian/Picard/IdentityComponent.lean` has exactly **6 residual `sorry`**, and all 6 are substrate-blocked, not proof-search:\n\n- **5 are FGA-tainted** \u2014 `Pic0Scheme` (L993), `degree` (L1034), `isAbelianVariety` (L1087), `finrank_eq_genus` (L1105), `kPoints_iff_kerDegree` (L1130). Each references `PicScheme C`, whose foundation `picSharp` in `FGAPicRepresentability.lean` is still `Classical.choice \u27e8sorry\u27e9`. They cannot be axiom-clean until the FGA representability rewire lands.\n- **1 is EGA-blocked** \u2014 `isFiniteTypeGeometricallyIrreducible` (L794): the `QuasiCompact \u2227 GeometricallyIrreducible` conjunct needs EGA IV\u2082 4.6.1 (reduced group-scheme product) + generic smoothness over `k\u0304` + EGA I 6.1.10, none in v4.31 Mathlib. Attemptable but a large substrate build, not a quick close.\n\nA Horizon session confined to `IdentityComponent*.lean` (T5s write-set) therefore has only the heavy geom-irred leaf to attempt, and cannot touch the 5 that matter.\n\n**Recommendation:** run the **`AJC.picrep`** milestone (`horizon run AJC.picrep`). Its concrete next step \u2014 rewiring FGA `picSharp` onto the sorry-free `relPresheaf` (`RelPicFunctor.lean`), via the Kleiman \u00a72 `k`-rational-section route \u2014 unblocks all 5 FGA-tainted `IdentityComponent` sorries **and** `tangentSpaceIso` (T10 / `AJC.pic0av`) at once. Details in the roadmap comment I just added to `AJC.picrep` and open issue `I-0062`.",
